 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
    StyleBox["e",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ";", 
     StyleBox["R",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.81307809350165*^9, 3.8130781609264364`*^9}, 
    3.8130782039890594`*^9, {3.813078272672757*^9, 3.8130783323990836`*^9}, {
    3.8130788081537347`*^9, 3.8130788107416773`*^9}, {3.813084082642866*^9, 
    3.8130840836064095`*^9}, 3.813222203505035*^9, {3.813222251629841*^9, 
    3.8132222597207966`*^9}, {3.8153288232903967`*^9, 3.815328825282467*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"68103cac-1622-4523-899a-4df2598fb5c9"],
 "is the electronic wavefunction and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.81307809350165*^9, 3.8130781609264364`*^9}, 
    3.8130782039890594`*^9, {3.813078272672757*^9, 3.8130783323990836`*^9}, {
    3.8130788081537347`*^9, 3.8130788107416773`*^9}, {3.813084082642866*^9, 
    3.8130840836064095`*^9}, 3.813222203505035*^9, {3.813222251629841*^9, 
    3.8132222597207966`*^9}, {3.8153288232903967`*^9, 3.815328825282467*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"576181b8-9812-4088-ac45-48223b3f7306"],
 "is the nuclear wavefunction. Within this contribution, we can take the \
total energy of the system (molecules) as the sum of the electronic, \
vibrational, rotational, and translational contributions,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8153288299231586`*^9, 3.815328944967827*^9}, {
  3.815329274154355*^9, 
  3.815329305917289*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a402f702-b867-4e96-85f7-\
d6093272ffcb"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["tot",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["e",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["vib",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["rot",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["trans",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81307809350165*^9, 3.8130781609264364`*^9}, 
   3.8130782039890594`*^9, {3.813078272672757*^9, 3.8130783323990836`*^9}, {
   3.8130788081537347`*^9, 3.8130788107416773`*^9}, {3.813082960788761*^9, 
   3.8130829717709465`*^9}, {3.8130830114286995`*^9, 
   3.8130830511844254`*^9}, {3.813083923369066*^9, 3.813083930891937*^9}, {
   3.8132222114766717`*^9, 3.8132222127335887`*^9}, {3.8132271828852577`*^9, 
   3.8132271927822623`*^9}, {3.8153289813630953`*^9, 
   3.8153289864065866`*^9}, {3.8153291213105726`*^9, 3.815329121718901*^9}, {
   3.815329313356747*^9, 
   3.815329332339172*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ee5ae816-92fd-403f-a880-\
c34604335a46"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s neglect the translational contributions for the \
moment. Each of the remaining contributions to the energy will have \
associated eigenstates given by the shape of the potential and/or the \
boundary conditions. For a diatomic molecule, we can visualize these \
molecular states in a potential energy diagram as shown in Figure 13.1. In \
this figure, the energies of the electronic, vibrational, and rotational \
eigenstates (plotted as horizontal bars) are superimposed on the electronic \
potential energy functions ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["e",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.81307809350165*^9, 3.8130781609264364`*^9}, 
    3.8130782039890594`*^9, {3.813078272672757*^9, 3.8130783323990836`*^9}, {
    3.8130788081537347`*^9, 3.8130788107416773`*^9}, {3.813082960788761*^9, 
    3.8130829717709465`*^9}, {3.8130830114286995`*^9, 
    3.8130830511844254`*^9}, {3.813083923369066*^9, 3.813083930891937*^9}, {
    3.8132222114766717`*^9, 3.8132222127335887`*^9}, {3.8132271828852577`*^9, 
    3.8132271927822623`*^9}, {3.8153289813630953`*^9, 
    3.8153289864065866`*^9}, {3.8153291213105726`*^9, 3.815329121718901*^9}, {
    3.815329313356747*^9, 3.815329332339172*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "ffd7fde8-70e2-4e78-9c27-5c75e82b064c"],
 "for different electronic states. Each of these molecular eigenstates will \
have a distinct wavefunction and thus distinct properties. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8153293923281927`*^9, 3.81532964833936*^9}, {
   3.815329684558172*^9, 3.8153299086191063`*^9}, {3.8153301582624545`*^9, 
   3.815330190733671*^9}, 
   3.9398953284262543`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"78e08eac-f097-45e9-b0df-\
891553ef2d14"],

