    3.8153289864065866`*^9}, {3.8153291213105726`*^9, 3.815329121718901*^9}, {
    3.815329313356747*^9, 3.815329332339172*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "1d5dbe17-e507-40e0-8a7a-c69e6ade6d41"],
 "(blue lines). OpenStax, CC BY 3.0"
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
   3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
   3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.809510876137825*^9, 3.809510907739876*^9}, {
   3.809968073566992*^9, 3.8099681536568317`*^9}, {3.810557260250428*^9, 
   3.8105572606139913`*^9}, {3.8130835305386977`*^9, 
   3.8130836194514275`*^9}, {3.813224407772764*^9, 3.8132244817756805`*^9}, {
   3.8153299652849884`*^9, 3.8153300856368465`*^9}, 
   3.9398953290521545`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"d8b53299-ed50-491c-b35a-\
2461685f83ff"],

Cell["\<\
At this point in your training as chemists, you are likely aware that \
transitions between these molecular eigenstates are associated with the \
emission or absorption of light, and we can monitor these processes to probe \
the structure and property of molecules in a variety of techniques that we \
collectively refer to as spectroscopy. In this lesson, we will address both \
fundamental issues of light-matter interaction (why does light of energy \
equal to the level spacing excite transitions?) and more practical aspects of \
spectroscopy (how do we interpret electronic spectra?). In all areas, we will \
provide only a general overview.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8153302013158503`*^9, 
  3.8153305685906115`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a02b0eb7-a671-4a12-a41e-\
e8c9f5308dda"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
The Harmonic Oscillator and Rigid Rotor as a Model for Molecular Vibrations \
and Rotations\
\>", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8095036018241525`*^9, 3.8095036081357145`*^9}, {
  3.8099672228815093`*^9, 3.8099672419464555`*^9}, {3.9208006160865035`*^9, 
  3.9208006230473022`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3c901b52-abd8-4e4e-b273-\
6f3cfc688d45"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Why the Rigid Rotor?", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.920800632477889*^9, 
  3.920800635419571*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ba2d8221-3349-f64f-a09d-\
c2135393b7c9"],

Cell["\<\
We can directly apply the rigid rotor model to interpret the rotational \
energy levels of a diatomic molecule. The plot in Figure 13.1 does not \
display the angular dependence of the electronic energy, only the dependence \
on internuclear distance. However, we can certainly assume that the molecule \
will also be rotating in space, and we can account for this by using the \
rigid rotor model, wherein we assume that rotation is separate from vibration.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810118613479906*^9, 3.810118737096867*^9}, {
  3.920800644891475*^9, 3.920800728323493*^9}, {3.920801145372437*^9, 
  3.9208011463259444`*^9}, {3.9398965115646667`*^9, 
  3.9398965120715847`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0a4b97bb-466f-5749-92df-\
02c15493043f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Remember that there is no potential energy component for rotation, meaning \
that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    OverscriptBox["V", "^"], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b72f8849-be55-ee4c-b0df-cefa55ae63ce"],
 ", and the energy eigenvalues of the rigid rotor are given by"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9208007799152794`*^9, 
  3.920800826829483*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"71f89fd2-d0b5-5a40-891c-\
ab53d902da3c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox["E", "J"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox[
      SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
      RowBox[{"2", 
       StyleBox["I",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], 
     StyleBox["J",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["J",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["+",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], 
       StyleBox["1",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
     StyleBox["            ",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox["J",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "=", "0"}]}], ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", ",",
   " ", "..."}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
   3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
   3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
   3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
   3.8101179041283765`*^9}, 
   3.810118893408634*^9},ExpressionUUID->"f55ac64f-0107-4045-9ab7-\
13e5170f7c9c"],

Cell["\<\
In other words, the energies (and eigenfunctions) of rotation are quantized. \
Each energy level is actually degenerate, meaning that there are multiple \
eigenfunctions with the same energy, and the degeneracy is given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810117977261583*^9, 3.8101180519186845`*^9}, {
  3.810118114392614*^9, 3.810118136850959*^9}, {3.841418940951063*^9, 
  3.841418942371519*^9}, {3.92080084992595*^9, 
  3.920800868817764*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"42cca32f-c8f0-9344-93c2-\
ab24826a4f3b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox["g", "J"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"2", 
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
     StyleBox["+",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["1",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["            ",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}], "=", "0"}]}], ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", 
  ",", " ", "..."}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
  3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
  3.8101179041283765`*^9}, {3.8101181436662183`*^9, 
  3.8101181537719917`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"810404e9-0da0-f849-a783-\
1bb07581cd16"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Spacing Between Energy Levels in a Rigid Rotor", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.920801255444968*^9, 
  3.9208012701615543`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4f9e8397-3b90-7f48-a2af-\
8ff968d342ea"],

Cell["\<\
Usually at room temperature, only the ground vibrational state of a diatomic \
molecule is initially populated (the lowest energy eigenvalue within an \
electronic potential shown in Figure 13.1). In addition, the spacing between \
vibrational energy levels is constant (in the harmonic oscillator \
approximation - see below). As we discussed earlier in the course, the \
rotational energy levels of a molecule are a different case. The energy \
spacing between any two adjacent energy levels is given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101187447981005`*^9, 3.8101187765740833`*^9}, {
  3.9208012740596647`*^9, 3.920801359587335*^9}, {3.9208014635451794`*^9, 
  3.920801473637355*^9}, {3.9208821587819514`*^9, 3.9208821726909018`*^9}, {
  3.9398967118953705`*^9, 
  3.9398967123655434`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3297bd56-4994-404b-bf14-\
914be1182e42"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{"J", "+", "1"}]], "-", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["E",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "J"]}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
     RowBox[{"2", 
      StyleBox["I",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["+",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        StyleBox["1",
         FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["+",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        StyleBox["2",
         FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}], 
     StyleBox["-",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["+",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        StyleBox["1",
         FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}]}], 
    StyleBox["]",
     FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
  3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
  3.8101179041283765`*^9}, {3.810118784045661*^9, 3.8101188159834547`*^9}, {
  3.8101188693749995`*^9, 
  3.8101189018153963`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9ead4519-d0df-414c-b7d1-\
da03c4bdf231"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\t\t        ", 
  RowBox[{"=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["+",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["1",
       FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
  3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
  3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
  3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
  3.8101179041283765`*^9}, {3.810118784045661*^9, 3.8101188159834547`*^9}, {
  3.8101188693749995`*^9, 
  3.81011893238441*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5ac35785-3d0e-374a-9fad-\
cce5e0f831d1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "As ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " increases, the spacing between adjacent levels also increases. In \
addition, the difference in energy levels is much smaller than for \
vibrational or electronic states, and many of these states are populated at \
room temperature."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101189728584146`*^9, 3.8101189846551237`*^9}, {
  3.810119018563933*^9, 3.810119060555586*^9}, {3.920801479237743*^9, 
  3.9208015308200455`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f8f8adf1-fe65-0a40-9c92-\
5549b0f0a5b5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Why the Harmonic Oscillator?", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.920478403684396*^9, 
  3.920478409195838*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"988d91e0-67ad-424e-b287-\
3a50cada88f3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let us consider the electronic energy functions ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["E", "e"], "(", "R", ")"}], " "}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"7c87cf53-5834-5346-b4e7-338d4afb284e"],
 "shown in Figure 13.1. Again, this function serves as the potential energy \
component of the Hamiltonian for the positions of the nuclei,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.920478413412341*^9, 3.920478519379136*^9}, {
   3.9204785797077413`*^9, 3.9204786123207664`*^9}, {3.920478714133089*^9, 
   3.9204787159430847`*^9}, {3.920479003686598*^9, 3.9204790053210015`*^9}, {
   3.920646241240103*^9, 3.920646259343978*^9}, {3.920646298668617*^9, 
   3.9206463492159147`*^9}, 3.9206464642899227`*^9, {3.939899032597826*^9, 
   3.9398990327722473`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"658ada55-cd61-3a42-9e84-\
aa8dd247fe96"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"[", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      OverscriptBox[
       StyleBox["T",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
      StyleBox["N",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["E",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["e",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], 
    StyleBox["]",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["tot",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
   3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.813223201970694*^9, 
   3.8132232122467637`*^9}, {3.813223607071082*^9, 3.813223609461746*^9}, 
   3.813225540628809*^9, 
   3.920479080701607*^9},ExpressionUUID->"9923cbd0-ca81-f440-bfbf-\
1b3abcd88eac"],

Cell["\<\
If we neglect any net movement of the molecule in space, we can write the \
nuclear wavefunction in terms of internal coordinates\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8135831371109495`*^9, 
  3.813583192965719*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"edfdcffe-9ab3-9c40-8867-\
9959fbd5912e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"[", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      OverscriptBox[
       StyleBox["T",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
      StyleBox["N",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["e",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       StyleBox["R",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]}], 
    StyleBox["]",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["R",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", "\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["tot",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["R",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", "\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
   3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.813223201970694*^9, 
   3.8132232122467637`*^9}, {3.813223607071082*^9, 3.813223609461746*^9}, 
   3.813225540628809*^9, {3.8135831213687415`*^9, 3.8135831308775077`*^9}, {
   3.813583199929793*^9, 3.81358323187179*^9}, {3.92047903694748*^9, 
   3.9204790390883055`*^9}, 3.920479085149889*^9, 
   3.9207315309377584`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"c98b4251-0b49-9e4b-86fe-\
72c24c0b6802"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The \[Theta] and \[Phi] dependence would describe any rotation of the \
molecule. Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s focus on only the dependence on the \
internuclear distance ",
 StyleBox["R,",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8135832350193467`*^9, 3.8135832942064285`*^9}, {
  3.813583419444499*^9, 
  3.8135834264309187`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3d51de2e-3e58-1a45-994d-\
4bdc370bd8e7"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"[", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      OverscriptBox[
       StyleBox["T",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "^"], 
      StyleBox["N",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]], "+", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["E",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["e",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       StyleBox["R",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}]}], 
    StyleBox["]",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"], 
   StyleBox[
    RowBox[{"(", "R", ")"}],
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["tot",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"], 
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
   3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.813223201970694*^9, 
   3.8132232122467637`*^9}, {3.813223607071082*^9, 3.813223609461746*^9}, 
   3.813225540628809*^9, {3.8135831213687415`*^9, 3.8135831308775077`*^9}, {
   3.813583199929793*^9, 3.81358323187179*^9}, {3.813583306245748*^9, 
   3.813583339244683*^9}, {3.9206463968952465`*^9, 
   3.9206464025019803`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7ad23858-a8df-f14b-9959-\
0bf3d7b5fc27"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["", "\[Prime]"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a9a15b7-463d-ac4d-9f07-9d042e5c4f0b"],
 " symbol denotes the portion of the wavefunction depending only on \
internuclear distance. Neglecting rotation and translation, this potential \
energy function determines the vibrational eigenstates and eigenfunctions of \
the molecule. The eigenvalues ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubsuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["tot",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
    3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.813223201970694*^9, 
    3.8132232122467637`*^9}, {3.813223607071082*^9, 3.813223609461746*^9}, 
    3.813225540628809*^9, {3.8135831213687415`*^9, 3.8135831308775077`*^9}, {
    3.813583199929793*^9, 3.81358323187179*^9}, {3.813583306245748*^9, 
    3.813583339244683*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "44c6421f-3138-884f-b8a7-0939c7d0d053"],
 " give the vibrational eigenstates (vibrational energy levels) of a \
molecule, and the eigenfunctions ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
    3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.813223201970694*^9, 
    3.8132232122467637`*^9}, {3.813223607071082*^9, 3.813223609461746*^9}, 
    3.813225540628809*^9, {3.8135831213687415`*^9, 3.8135831308775077`*^9}, {
    3.813583199929793*^9, 3.81358323187179*^9}, {3.813583306245748*^9, 
    3.813583339244683*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "e64ece1a-92f8-9447-a04f-648755574af5"],
 "give the vibrational nuclear wavefunction, with the absolute square of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "'"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
    3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.813223201970694*^9, 
    3.8132232122467637`*^9}, {3.813223607071082*^9, 3.813223609461746*^9}, 
    3.813225540628809*^9, {3.8135831213687415`*^9, 3.8135831308775077`*^9}, {
    3.813583199929793*^9, 3.81358323187179*^9}, {3.813583306245748*^9, 
    3.813583339244683*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "e86837c2-025e-4749-b52c-a10476da8a00"],
 "giving the probability of finding the nuclei with internuclear distance ",
 StyleBox["R",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". We will see that the harmonic oscillator provides a good approximation to \
the true form of the function ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["E", "e"], "(", "R", ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2e0ee915-05ca-8d43-a101-64aa8bbc4da5"],
 " for many systems, providing an easy method to calculate both the \
vibrational eigenvalues and eigenfunctions."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.814709087140006*^9, 3.814709225038685*^9}, {
  3.9204791821310825`*^9, 3.9204792059244027`*^9}, {3.920646472239328*^9, 
  3.9206465959920225`*^9}, {3.9207315783918357`*^9, 3.920731591308222*^9}, {
  3.920731777894391*^9, 3.9207317950329523`*^9}, {3.920732049503812*^9, 
  3.920732068003523*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"681526e1-a6f0-854e-88c7-\
49876b5fc6a6"]
}, Open  ]],

