}, {2}]],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 13.3",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". The solutions to the harmonic oscillator approximation for a model \
diatomic, plotting the absolute square of the wavefunction, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[RightBracketingBar]", 
    RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "(", "x", ")"}], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[LeftBracketingBar]", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"bb64ba13-9867-b142-a4ba-31c78353cb98"],
 " (blue), offset by the energies along the potential. The approximation is \
better for the lower-energy states because the real potential more closely \
corresponds to a harmonic potential at lower energies."
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
  3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
  3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.809510876137825*^9, 3.809510907739876*^9}, {
  3.809968073566992*^9, 3.8099681536568317`*^9}, {3.8099700491335783`*^9, 
  3.80997004921373*^9}, {3.80997007975782*^9, 3.8099701752275105`*^9}, {
  3.8412240899354286`*^9, 3.841224090292589*^9}, {3.920646793511657*^9, 
  3.9206467936632986`*^9}, {3.939900464414385*^9, 
  3.9399004647175846`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"19357967-7cf8-5e47-9266-\
5b94f67f2b9f"],

Cell["\<\
It turns out that this approximation works well not only for diatomic \
molecules but for really almost any molecular vibration. If you calculate the \
vibrational frequencies of a molecule using some computational chemistry \
program, the software will certainly use the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]harmonic \
approximation\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], that is, approximating the vibrational \
potentials to be harmonic. However, these vibrations don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t \
always correspond to just two atoms moving apart; in larger molecules, they \
typically involve the motion of many atoms. These vibrations are found as \
what we call the normal modes of a coupled system of harmonic oscillators, \
but we won\[CloseCurlyQuote]t discuss how these normal modes are found in \
this course.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9206469836079855`*^9, 
  3.920647016184433*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"aed60775-9be9-334d-a382-\
54f31da8515e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
An Improved Approximation for Diatomic Molecules: The Morse Potential\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8099673330453844`*^9, 3.8099673448804846`*^9}, {
  3.9206475197203326`*^9, 
  3.9206475675334673`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"abb71288-631b-fe40-bb07-\
b76bf36dc07b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "As seen in Figures 13.2 and 13.3, the harmonic oscillator approximation is \
not very accurate at extended internuclear distances (large values of ",
 StyleBox["R",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "). In these regions, the harmonic potential continues to increase, whereas \
the true potential levels off as the nuclei approach infinite separation. As \
a result, the harmonic approximation is not very accurate for higher energy \
eigenvalues and cannot correctly predict the dissociation of the molecule \
(all energy eigenvalues are stable within the harmonic potential). An \
improved model of the potential for diatomic molecules is provided by the \
Morse potential,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.92064757961127*^9, 3.9206476467442317`*^9}, {
  3.920647749580188*^9, 3.9206478900069513`*^9}, {3.9207327921065607`*^9, 
  3.9207327929149904`*^9}, {3.93990109408914*^9, 
  3.939901096303524*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"59484240-9293-b243-bf5d-\
817a8eb9f0c1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"V", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["R",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["D",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["e",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["1",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["-",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["e",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "\[Beta]"}], 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
          StyleBox["R",
           FontSlant->"Italic"], 
          StyleBox["-",
           FontSlant->"Italic"], 
          SubscriptBox[
           StyleBox["R",
            FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]}], ")"}]}]]}], ")"}], 
    "2"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8102958629799924`*^9, 3.810295912892226*^9}, 
   3.873192471340421*^9, {3.920647907330737*^9, 
   3.9206479215521364`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"01baf121-a4fe-c341-ab3a-\
40019e92a5ef"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["D",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["e",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]],
   FontSlant->"Italic"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8102958629799924`*^9, 3.810295912892226*^9}, 
    3.873192471340421*^9, {3.920647907330737*^9, 3.9206479215521364`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"ce5ad803-53df-fa4f-b373-f7df0c98f602"],
 " is the dissociation energy, the energy at which the molecule dissociates, \
and \[Beta] describes the shape of the curve around the equilibrium \
internuclear distance ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["R",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "0"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8102958629799924`*^9, 3.810295912892226*^9}, 
    3.873192471340421*^9, {3.920647907330737*^9, 3.9206479215521364`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"6d3b3653-fe79-4b40-82bc-ac39354fcc06"],
 ". The energy eigenvalues of the Morse potential are given by "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.920647925638405*^9, 3.920648046378078*^9}, 
   3.920732809412561*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b7109303-f485-5946-bbdb-\
74f5fcd740f3"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["E",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["n",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[HBar]", 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        FractionBox[
         StyleBox["k",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Mu]"], ")"}], 
       RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["n",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "+", 
        FractionBox["1", "2"]}], ")"}]}], "-", 
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox[
       SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"], 
       RowBox[{"4", 
        StyleBox[
         SubscriptBox["D", "e"],
         FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox[
        StyleBox["k",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Mu]"], ")"}], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["n",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], "+", 
         FractionBox["1", "2"]}], ")"}], "2"], "          ", 
      StyleBox["n",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}], "=", "0"}]}], ",", "1", ",", 
  RowBox[{"2", "..."}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8105604123102984`*^9, 3.8105604953152647`*^9}, {
   3.810560625658684*^9, 3.810560663188472*^9}, {3.8105607210337563`*^9, 
   3.8105607559921465`*^9}, 
   3.9206480623813457`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"bdc41aa2-e901-8940-8422-\
62a5aa5b81b5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where the upper limit of the integer ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is given by the condition that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["n",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8105604123102984`*^9, 3.8105604953152647`*^9}, {
   3.810560625658684*^9, 3.810560663188472*^9}, {3.8105607210337563`*^9, 
   3.8105607559921465`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "7d06f98a-0e8a-7241-aef6-645ca0e80049"],
 "<",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{" ", 
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox["D", "e"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8105604123102984`*^9, 3.8105604953152647`*^9}, {
   3.810560625658684*^9, 3.810560663188472*^9}, {3.8105607210337563`*^9, 
   3.8105607559921465`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "614f12eb-85fa-b343-9ccb-ec4fe01056ea"],
 ". Shown in Figure 13.4 are the eigenfunctions and eigenvalues of the Morse \
potential. There are two important differences from the harmonic oscillator \
to note. First, the spacing between energy levels is not constant but rather \
decreases as ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " increases. Second, the amplitude of the wavefunction increases at larger \
values of ",
 StyleBox["R",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " as ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " increases, meaning that the most probable bond length also increases with \
increasing energy."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9206480740206957`*^9, 3.9206480946184826`*^9}, {
  3.9206483773692656`*^9, 3.9206485560879216`*^9}, {3.9207328358288565`*^9, 
  3.9207328359646435`*^9}, {3.939901250187027*^9, 
  3.939901250338297*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6b8dc518-b997-064c-a131-\
34a38e448aa3"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[HBar]", "=", "1"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "=", "1"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"De", "=", "50"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"a", "=", "2"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Lambda]", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"2", "*", "\[Mu]", "*", "De"}], ")"}], "^", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], ")"}]}], "/", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"a", "*", "\[HBar]"}], ")"}]}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"z", "=", 
   RowBox[{"2", "*", "\[Lambda]", "*", 
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
     RowBox[{"-", "x"}]]}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"norm", "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"n", "!"}], "*", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"2", "\[Lambda]"}], "-", 
         RowBox[{"2", "n"}], "-", "1"}], ")"}]}], 
      RowBox[{"Gamma", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"2", "\[Lambda]"}], "-", "n"}], "]"}]], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"norm", "*", 
    SuperscriptBox["z", 
     RowBox[{"\[Lambda]", "-", "n", "-", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}]], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], ")"}]}], "z"}]], 
    RowBox[{"LaguerreL", "[", 
     RowBox[{"n", ",", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"2", "\[Lambda]"}], "-", 
       RowBox[{"2", "n"}], "-", "1"}], ",", "z"}], "]"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Epsilon]", "=", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"\[Lambda]", "-", "n", "-", 
         RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}], ")"}], "^", "2"}]}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"n", ",", "0", ",", "5"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"energies", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"a", "^", "2"}], "*", 
        RowBox[{"\[HBar]", "^", "2"}]}], ")"}], "/", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"2", "*", "\[Mu]"}], ")"}]}], ")"}], "*", "\[Epsilon]"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"harmenergies", "=", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[HBar]", 
       StyleBox["*",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["(",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], 
         RowBox[{"De", "*", 
          RowBox[{"a", "^", "2"}], "*", 
          RowBox[{"2", "/", "\[Mu]"}]}], ")"}], "^", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], ")"}]}], 
       StyleBox["*",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], 
       RowBox[{"(", 
