Cell[TextData[{
 "Note that the probability to be in the final state |",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\[RightAngleBracket] increases linearly with time. This approximation, \
however, assumes a small value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["c", 
     StyleBox["m",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox[
      RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}],
      FontSlant->"Plain"]], 
    RowBox[{"(", "t", ")"}]}],
   FontSlant->"Italic"]],
  CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJwdxVtIU3EAB+BtmlPmw+wyTyiu2UJb00lGDXHSZoENM01U0A1REF88iXkp
HYmC0zBRKwIpikAwl5aMqah4aUQdPV7QqRFelgYtnFNEobKty/93Hj4+WWHp
zSIBj8eLIrAzw+o9le/RmkTa4zJyVEqDPY1sYBwfsaRdNYtTlpgFnOOZ8uFZ
cR//BjmsgA7Acz0/hXjXuhGNXWN557B5rzsee8yyC/hiry0BF7tpDVZHy7Nx
6kSnEe8nr7Ba2qOVHsucx3KR+RPuund0DVOv4kU6ctXqazE+ad2WY+Gi8Awe
965fwjVfNhPx55gnp5PJIRNtCpyo+cHSZLY1Yg531NcE3iJbvnuDMNWfI8FJ
h+MUvvz4vBEPGl9w5wbYerCeVQ/j0JFaFvv7DU7jdLf/YRn5brbrDy4KMwXf
JhdKDWJ8NWiIxgb9RjVu0Zne4PCvTu5uO38AR85ouKuM/FEsUl5/h3U6B4N7
Q+wsVj7aEpSTG23FfjhSVXAC+2JbJditbrBUkFNLqLdYr/gwhv82VrzHqoGX
dyrJGdTZalznfHgfs65/3Nbctmd4MqupE/e3xzG4ZXmVW9FxZBk/bZZ+w12V
Bzv42sKDfRz+u+QXvvKc8eH/Q/I1yA==
   "],ExpressionUUID->"48528bc2-be93-49ca-b34f-23badc8f53a4"],
 ", so it becomes invalid if this probability is large. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8154871889671116`*^9, 3.815487250220689*^9}, {
  3.815487282477705*^9, 
  3.8154872863407106`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3f6d2e4b-cf34-466d-8bdd-\
923bdbcc3d84"],

Cell["\<\
We now have a fundamental basis for the requirement we have always discussed \
regarding transitions between eigenstates and their relation to the frequency \
(and thus energy) of the incident radiation: the energy of the light must \
match the difference in energy of the eigenstates to have a high probability \
of absorption.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8154873251305475`*^9, 
