Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Dipole Moment and Transition Probability", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8157539702209845`*^9, 
  3.8157539903955245`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dcf170a6-8a9e-41ba-9134-\
b2640ace402c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Equation (45) gives an expression for the probability of finding a system \
in state |",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\[RightAngleBracket] following interaction with a sinusoidal potential. For \
the case of interaction with light, the previous section focused on the \
requirement that the energy of the light equal the difference in energy \
between the two states. However, we have not yet discussed the influence of \
the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["V",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["mk",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJwdxVkow3EAB/ANGc3D5pi/CGNyWyGWTDYpLbei2BIlL/7kPhalzJMQKU9S
is3ZGkKMJZa/I1eSmwcyS/JAa8jvu4dPH2FlXWGVE4vFEhL4rkBvDy63ytRc
mbeQHJ7VY8olK82nu1gwKD7EWefmE1xi3fvBh7wFdh7Zv4J2xUcz3xz8rn+I
wM8bZdFY86FNwFaNMBEnzRpScLWFlmJJhKgYZ29OqPBnxhUjo62yIK+iYyzi
ai7wZKfnDaamErhycsv1NA/76d9EmHPGCcNG+20y7rh/TMWXsSOhGWT+5kAU
TpV+MTSZ6Q88wqPdHW61ZN2L3R1TiyUCnGYzUjh9OF6Fl1VjjktdDTNYwUhW
se9aF4NdnJf3cb7FxVZPbit+/sVV/mqPBnJlkJKHM91XaKxUPLTjPrl6Dgc8
3TnWmthLOORA6rhFxV7H3JicLSyXn5rxLN/E4JihV6dGcq+h2hmHiCt88E9c
vwBbJD26JnJ2DTWPFVE7G/ivt2kbi5fGW5vJBVRkO/4HJEr/Iw==
   "],ExpressionUUID->"d458bad7-b6af-4395-a745-0120aa2edda9"],
 " term on the transition probability. For linearly polarized light, this \
term depends on the projection of the molecular electric dipole moment onto \
the electric field vector, which is given by the scalar product"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815754040458627*^9, 3.815754270251176*^9}, {
  3.815754334925294*^9, 3.815754389197176*^9}, {3.8157544311173286`*^9, 
