   3.810118893408634*^9},ExpressionUUID->"3ef66fee-05f6-47da-8da8-\
a47f9ea220e3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Now we will use the perturbation theory equations derived in the previous \
sections to investigate the origins of this selection rule for rigid-rotor \
diatomic molecules. First, let us assume that a molecule is interacting with \
linear-polarized light whose electric field points along some arbitrary ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "-axis in the laboratory frame. Equation (48) then becomes"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8157579823878517`*^9, 3.8157580269680777`*^9}, {
   3.8157582073016415`*^9, 3.8157582560731173`*^9}, 3.8157590715101757`*^9, {
   3.847370523151887*^9, 3.847370523581891*^9}, {3.940077351433777*^9, 
   3.9400773522600384`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"817bacc5-9e8e-4706-9839-\
598831539027"],

