Cell["\<\
Importantly, notice that if the magnitude of the molecular dipole moment is \
zero, then the transition dipole moment will also be zero, giving zero \
probability of a transition between states. This result is the origin of the \
requirement that molecules have a permanent dipole moment to observe a \
rotational spectrum. To solve the integral in equation (54), we must first \
break the spherical harmonics into their constituent components. Remember \
that spherical harmonics take the form\
\>", "Text",
