Cell[TextData[{
 "Because the Hermite polynomials are orthogonal, the integral in equation \
(67) will return a value of zero unless ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"n", "'"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"n", "\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "59a6e5cb-ff1d-495e-957d-231e578412a2"],
 ", giving the vibrational transition selection rule of"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8158305549940467`*^9, 3.8158306327360477`*^9}, {
  3.815831784398186*^9, 3.8158317875755653`*^9}, {3.9400887565212936`*^9, 
  3.9400887591123257`*^9}, {3.9400891857389545`*^9, 
  3.9400891863084316`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"21613360-6910-46bc-997f-\
b52231f4f89c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
    StyleBox["n",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]}]], "DisplayFormula",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815829768401164*^9, 3.8158297727278275`*^9}, {
  3.815830645919637*^9, 3.815830669888232*^9}, {3.8158317897752457`*^9, 
  3.815831790302328*^9}, {3.940088762848213*^9, 
  3.9400887634828854`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9649034b-1ef5-416a-9276-\
30767defd36b"],

Cell["\<\
Note that this rule is valid only when we ignore higher-order terms in the \
Taylor series expansion and assume a harmonic oscillator wavefunction, so \
other transitions are possible in real systems, but the probability of the \
transition (and thus the intensity of the band in a spectrum) will be much \
smaller than for the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]allowed\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
transitions.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815831818610017*^9, 3.8158318388021336`*^9}, {
  3.8158318702652445`*^9, 3.815831948515837*^9}, {3.815837267257413*^9, 
  3.815837269014609*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"941d501c-48ed-427b-bac2-\
6c3bedcbe64d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Selection Rules for Electronic Transitions", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8158276864162436`*^9, 3.815827696815858*^9}, {
  3.8158398580315876`*^9, 
  3.8158398722009106`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"68b64e64-9b15-4806-b100-\
0fc226a41e3d"],

Cell["\<\
The selection rules for electronic transitions are a bit more complicated \
than those for the rigid rotor/harmonic oscillator model. This complexity \
results from the fact that the transition dipole moment now also depends on \
the electronic component of the wavefunction (as opposed to just the nuclear \
component in the cases studied thus far). We can write the transition dipole \
moment as\
\>", "Text",
