57183e7b80ae"],

Cell["\<\
Note that the vibrational wavefunctions here are in different electronic \
states and thus are not necessarily orthogonal. In fact, this equation shows \
that the transition dipole moment depends on the overlap between the initial \
and final vibrational wavefunctions, which is the basis of the Franck-Condon \
principle. The selection rules for the electronic component are more \
complicated, and we won\[CloseCurlyQuote]t cover them in more detail at this \
moment. We went over some of these rules in the lesson on multielectron atoms.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815846648071972*^9, 3.815846722683859*^9}, {
  3.815846816293152*^9, 3.8158468960315714`*^9}, {3.815847355919318*^9, 
  3.8158473613020315`*^9}, {3.8158474052080545`*^9, 3.8158474063241167`*^9}, {
  3.9400898265403576`*^9, 
  3.9400898309071293`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2f4601b9-8c00-493c-a42a-\
834f4e04ed6c"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

