Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 13.6",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Idealized rotational spectrum of a rigid rotor, where each spectral line \
corresponds to a transition between state ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and state ",
 StyleBox["J ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "+ 1. Changing the temperature alters the initial state population \
distribution, thereby altering the spectrum. Wolfram Demonstrations, Porscha \
McRobbie and Eitan Geva (March 2011), CC BY-NC-SA, \
https://demonstrations.wolfram.com/\
TemperatureDependentRotationalEnergySpectrum/"
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
   3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
   3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.809510876137825*^9, 3.809510907739876*^9}, {
   3.809968073566992*^9, 3.8099681536568317`*^9}, {3.810557260250428*^9, 
   3.8105572606139913`*^9}, {3.8130835305386977`*^9, 
   3.8130836194514275`*^9}, {3.813224407772764*^9, 3.8132244817756805`*^9}, {
   3.8153299652849884`*^9, 3.8153300856368465`*^9}, {3.815486734293851*^9, 
   3.8154867344058456`*^9}, {3.8154879218419533`*^9, 
   3.8154879663632336`*^9}, {3.815923898141548*^9, 3.8159239219760113`*^9}, {
   3.815923956762824*^9, 3.8159240452391195`*^9}, {3.8159247099333353`*^9, 
   3.8159247404817953`*^9}, 3.815994726716399*^9, 3.9398953332138424`*^9, {
   3.940090286614212*^9, 
   3.940090287208294*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"203c6893-3b40-43a3-a939-\
00e65c881b32"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The true spacing of bands decreases with ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " due to a phenomenon known as centrifugal distortion, in which the \
increasing angular momentum leads to an increase in the bond length and a \
decrease in the energy spacing relative to an ideal rigid rotor."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815924749518552*^9, 3.815924884817029*^9}, 
   3.940090417436901*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b09d3084-ddb7-42a1-8ecd-\
e753f18ae1af"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Beyond the Linear Rigid Rotor", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815924940961282*^9, 
  3.8159249451488843`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1de90593-0821-4db8-9bb9-\
baa5dfd22d6c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Of course, there are many molecules that are nonlinear, and the rotational \
spectrum cannot be accurately represented by a single rigid rotor. Although \
we won\[CloseCurlyQuote]t cover the properties of the rotational spectra of \
such polyatomic molecules in detail, we provide a brief overview here. In \
short, the moment of inertia can always be represented in a molecule-based \
coordinate system with axes ",
 StyleBox["a",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["b",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and ",
 StyleBox["c ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "by the three components ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["I", "a"], ",", " ", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "b"], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"and", " ", 
     SubscriptBox["I", "c"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c538c195-c379-4423-9b03-d358f7da9735"],
 ", where by convention"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815924950186002*^9, 3.8159249829421835`*^9}, {
  3.8159250142923727`*^9, 3.8159250568241663`*^9}, {3.81592513902519*^9, 
  3.815925311358305*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d6c09ff5-c6a0-4ab6-ac82-\
06df6c55c186"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["I",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["a",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "\[LessEqual]", 
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["I",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["b",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "\[LessEqual]", 
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["I",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["c",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815925507606925*^9, 
  3.8159255361675787`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"152ea31a-d2d1-4e42-accf-\
2ee670e51e1d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "There are then four classes of molecules that are defined by the values of \
the moment of inertia: linear, spherical top, symmetric top, and asymmetric \
tops. Linear molecules have moment of inertia ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    RowBox[{"<<", 
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["I",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["b",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}], "=", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["I",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["c",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.815925507606925*^9, 3.8159255361675787`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"95860ae7-a8b1-4cb1-b4f3-01da700074a2"],
 " and behave as rigid rotors. Spherical tops have moment of inertia ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["I",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["a",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["b",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["c",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.815925507606925*^9, 3.8159255361675787`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"b788173c-9b79-4b98-aaed-8f68c7aa9d4f"],
 " and have the same energy levels as a rigid rotor (albeit with a greater \
number of degenerate states). Note that spherical tops do not have a dipole \
moment, so they don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t typically have a pure rotational \
spectrum."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8159256818459644`*^9, 3.8159258596351542`*^9}, {
  3.8159260021600018`*^9, 3.815926010834999*^9}, {3.815984322412331*^9, 
  3.8159844030083904`*^9}, {3.8159848018623605`*^9, 3.8159848263443317`*^9}, {
  3.8160069317306275`*^9, 
  3.816006932036563*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"aa227b45-5d5e-4256-a273-\
dc5feca317fd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Symmetric top molecules have two moment of inertia that are the same, \
either ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["I",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["a",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["b",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "<", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["c",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.815925507606925*^9, 3.8159255361675787`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"ca2d5d2c-90ba-464b-97e8-60e993207e1b"],
 " (oblate top) or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["a",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "<", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["b",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], "=", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["I",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["c",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.815925507606925*^9, 3.8159255361675787`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"902f92eb-01b0-48b5-acf0-a77f08a4da0a"],
 " (prolate top). The energy levels of each state are given by"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8159844076624794`*^9, 3.815984441723699*^9}, {
  3.8159844823810263`*^9, 3.815984578940067*^9}, {3.8159849191117153`*^9, 
  3.8159849256201553`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c8416ba1-5c5d-4cd4-a4a6-\
fdc979020c8f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox[
    SubscriptBox["E", "J"],
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["BJ",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["J",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], 
        StyleBox["+",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        StyleBox["1",
         FontSlant->"Plain"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Plain"]}]}], 
     StyleBox["+",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], 
       StyleBox[
        RowBox[{"A", "-", "B"}],
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox[")",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["K",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
      StyleBox["          ",
       FontSlant->"Plain"], 
      StyleBox["J",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}], "=", "0"}]}], ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", 
  ",", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"...", "        ", 
    StyleBox["K",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], "=", "0"}], ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "2", ",", "...",
   " "}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
   3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
   3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
   3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
   3.8101179041283765`*^9}, 3.810118893408634*^9, {3.8159849406744976`*^9, 
   3.8159850043543577`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"772d5954-2bbf-4cad-8538-\
b7713d6f3d23"],

Cell["where", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8159850095948334`*^9, 
  3.8159850099466953`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d93424dd-c9bf-46a6-9a16-\
09f466ea0290"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["B",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  FractionBox[
   StyleBox["h",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   RowBox[{"8", 
    SuperscriptBox["\[Pi]", "2"], 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["I",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["B",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
   3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
   3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
   3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
   3.8101179041283765`*^9}, 3.810118893408634*^9, {3.8159849406744976`*^9, 
   3.8159850461195765`*^9}, {3.8159850807281804`*^9, 
   3.815985097939887*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e7ecf402-8a63-480e-b611-\
6399300740e4"],

Cell["and ", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8159851119509068`*^9, 
  3.8159851123279147`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"18f53151-3f40-4305-b05f-\
91e701505bba"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["A",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     StyleBox["h",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{"8", 
      SuperscriptBox["\[Pi]", "2"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["I",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["A",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]], " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"prolate", " ", "top"}], ")"}], "                ", 
    StyleBox["A",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   StyleBox["=",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     StyleBox["h",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     RowBox[{"8", 
      SuperscriptBox["\[Pi]", "2"], 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["I",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["C",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]], " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"oblate", " ", "top"}], ")"}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8101146208354783`*^9, 3.810114640337751*^9}, {
   3.810114687183729*^9, 3.8101147298453236`*^9}, {3.810115960220513*^9, 
   3.810116006121975*^9}, {3.8101168075734625`*^9, 3.8101168261777344`*^9}, {
   3.81011776826762*^9, 3.8101177880720615`*^9}, {3.810117853857074*^9, 
   3.8101179041283765`*^9}, 3.810118893408634*^9, {3.8159849406744976`*^9, 
   3.8159850461195765`*^9}, {3.8159850807281804`*^9, 
   3.8159851561658525`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f1bbb483-c64c-4671-b8e9-\
7380a04875a0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Note that the spacing between ",
 StyleBox["J",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " levels for a given value of ",
 StyleBox["K",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is the same as for a linear rigid rotor (neglecting centrifugal \
distortion). "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8159851598157644`*^9, 
  3.8159852377363243`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"18f0d303-788f-488c-9ae5-\
233af0fc14e6"],

Cell["\<\
For an asymmetric top, there is no formula for calculating the energy levels. \
Instead, one must solve a matrix eigenvalue problem in a basis of the \
rotation matrix functions. We unfortunately don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have time \
to discuss this problem in more detail. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.815985240191226*^9, 3.8159852770109777`*^9}, {
  3.815985309680375*^9, 3.8159853111118593`*^9}, {3.815985431569296*^9, 
  3.815985444645265*^9}, {3.8159855307545023`*^9, 
  3.8159855522624826`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ef73903a-5b18-466d-a5a1-\
187cdbb34e34"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Rotational-Vibrational Spectra\t", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8159222610181875`*^9, 3.8159222754629087`*^9}, {
  3.8159857251692705`*^9, 
  3.815985735367471*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5b6eb5d3-4d30-4e6d-a99a-\
673628f9bea4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Previously when discussing vibrational transitions, we have neglected any \
rotational transitions. However, thinking back to the energy diagram in \
Figure 13.1, we see that rotational transitions always accompany vibrational \
transitions. The overall allowed transitions are subject to the selection \
rules for both vibrational and rotational states. An idealized \
rotational-vibrational spectrum for a single vibrational transitions of a \
linear rigid rotor is shown in Figure 13.7. Two series of rotational \
transitions are observed: those corresponding to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", " ", "J"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"+", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3e5ca6d1-81ce-434b-b00a-da70f54cc605"],
 " (the R-branch) and those corresponding to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", " ", "J"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ed922614-5f89-4d65-8ea5-c68ac6bbffb1"],
 " (the P-branch). If the ground state has nonzero orbital and/or spin \
angular momentum, then ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", " ", "J"}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"610172f1-38d2-4656-b679-c8ea93ee6e41"],
 " transitions are also allowed, giving a Q-branch."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8159947353216534`*^9, 3.8159948931854286`*^9}, {
  3.8159949273880835`*^9, 3.815995044745905*^9}, {3.8160012706088867`*^9, 
